Chile Stocks: Cap, Sudamericana de Vapores Fall; Cencosud Gains

-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 
2011-03-14T20:43:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-14/chilean-stocks-cap-cencosud-and-sudamericada-de-vapores-fall.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Chilean trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4:09 p.m. New York time.  The Ipsa index closed little changed at 4,325.12.    Cap SA (CAP)  ,  Chile ’s largest steelmaker and iron miner,
lost 0.6 percent to a six-month low of 20,885 pesos. Industrial
metal prices dropped on concern that demand from  Japan  may
weaken after last week’s earthquake and tsunami.  Cencosud SA (CENCOSUD CC) rose 1.1 percent to 3,168.1
pesos, ending a five-day losing streak. Horst Paulmann,
controller of Chile’s largest retailer by sales, may sell a 0.2
percent stake in the company to avoid forcing local pension
funds to reduce their stake to comply with local regulations, El
Mercurio reported.  Cia. Sudamericana de Vapores SA (VAPORES CC) retreated 4.1
percent to 310.91 pesos. Latin America’s largest container
shipping company is weighing options to deal with potential
“cash-flow problems” amid higher fuel costs and lower shipping
rates, it wrote in a statement today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
 ethomson1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
